5:
Ahh... Nothing like some peace and 
quiet. Wouldn't you agree?
8:
Yes, quite peaceful indeed. 
No incidents to speak of.
10:
You know, it's important to just take a 
load off every once in a while. 
Especially during moments like—
22: Cap'n... I can't do this anymore...
29:
Make way, scallywags! Ahem…
Marina, the Crimson Blade, at 
your service!
33: We didn't ask for your service!
37:
We didn't, but I'm glad to see you 
again, Marina.
41:
Hehe! Me too! 
I've missed both of your lovely faces!
48:
Mm-mmm! Now, THIS is some serious 
gourmet grub! 
You sure you weren't a chef in a 
previous life, Alk?
52:
I don't mean to pry, but how did you 
make it all the way here?
55: Isn't it obvious? I used a World Flipper.
57:
I figured if I flipped around a few times, 
I'd eventually find this place.
60:
Ngh... It was more than just a few 
times...
62:
Not to mention the hell we went 
through to get here...
64:
We saw SO many exotic worlds along 
the way! Not to mention the treasure! 
I oughta thank you all for the 
adventures we had!
67: What kind of worlds did you see?
70:
Where do I even begin? 
So many seas, so little time!
72:
Let's see... 
Our first venture took us to a snowy 
mountaintop.
77: That isn't even remotely close to a sea!
80:
And you wouldn't BELIEVE what 
happened next—a yeti attacked us! 
Oh, our battle was glorious!
82:
It went on for three straight days—
one of the biggest and loudest foes 
we've ever faced, that's for sure!
84:
But get this—turns out our yeti friend's 
got a golden set of pipes. 
So we asked him to sing a tune for us!
91:
So we partied it UP for three days 
straight! *sigh* I hope Yooie's doing 
well.
103:
After that, we ended up in a country of 
tiny people! 
Like, can you say JACKPOT?
105:
Kay, let me explain—I'd already read all 
about this once before in Gulliver's 
Travels, right? 
I knew just how to play my cards.
110:
Slow down... 
Who the hell is Gulliver?
113:
He's from a book Cap'n read once—
she thought she had it all figured out 
since she knew the story, but 
everything went to hell...
115:
Shut yer trap! I mean, yes, I suppose it 
didn't go EXACTLY as I imagined it 
would, but...
118:
At least we kept their country from 
sinking into the sea—that's a win in my 
book! 
Like, sometimes it's fun to be the good 
guys!
124:
So yeah... I guess you could say we've 
had our fair share of adventure 
recently. 
Figured it was time to lay low for a 
while, you know?
125:
Plus, visiting all those worlds got me 
thinking about you two.
136:
Yep! I wanted to know where you guys 
had been. Not only that, but what you'd 
seen and who you'd fought against!
138:
I started to think that maybe that's 
where my adventure was! 
Like, this is where I need to be. Catch 
my drift?
141:
Huh... 
All I'm doing is just helping Light 
though.
144: The same can be said for me.
147:
Well, call it a hunch on my part. 
You guys don't mind, do you? Nimbus? 
Light?
151:
You're gonna join us no matter what 
we say anyway, right? 
Do what you want, pirate.
154:
We'd appreciate your help, Captain. 
Just don't get Alk involved in any pirate 
business.
158:
Oh, I'd never! This calls for another 
feast—in the name of comradery!
167:
There's always more room in my 
tummy to party hardy!
171:
It seems things will be a little livelier 
from now on.
